<br>
I can see that Phytir had been camping the mob could be seen as that was his mob (within a guild anyway).  However, Vaniki requires some assistance besides just one pick up group and he called on his guild (Tinid Losi) to help.  Tind Losi came: vini, vedi, veci.  Loot was awarded by leadership to who has been contributing to the guild.  Tindi is fairly large and could have asked 2 or 3 groups of friends to come to help in tells as a safer option to guarantee loot I guess.<br>
<br>
I don't know what I would do if I were in the same shoes to award loot.  It would depend on if Phytir had been contributing to the guild efforts or just doing his own thing.  If you don't come to guild raids and then call your guild to kill a mob then you are kind of at the mercy of your leadership.  Tindi leadership could have said we can come as a guild but we get to award the loot.  Which would resulted in Phytir /guildremoving most likely.  No matter what if Phytir didn't get the loot, he wouldn't have been happy.<br>
<br>
I have experienced similar events in my own own guild.  Level xx main plays then switches mains.  Level xx alt plays to 60 gets a BP then goes back to playing original alt and starts asking for epic loot.  <br>
<br>
Later, we killed Vaniki and award to the most derserving tank there.  We post it on the website and the level 60 alt/main (who knows at this point) complains about someone getting the Willsapper besides him even though he wasn't there.  Can you believe that?  Lol.<br>
<br>
At first glance at the thread, I would say TL leadership screwed Phytir but as leadership in a guild, I would say that this is not black and white so walk a mile in another man's shoes.....<br>
